Input Output units management:

1. Interactivity level
The mode of interactivity may be active or not, with drawings or not,
with the using of a mouse or not.

2. Printing level
From 0 to 10, the number of printings may be reduced or augmented

3. Array addresses listing
To obtain the memory adress of each array or not.
Use it for debugging only.

4. Echo or not of taped input data values
The LU language interprets the data. 
The resulted value may be interesting, notably with User's functions.

5. Output redirection on a file
The displays a priori on screen, may be rediriged on a file.
Its name must be given after.

6. Input redirection from a file
All data saved on a file may be read and uses as data from the keyboard.
It is possible to constitute sets of data to construct objects.
The key word QUITTER or EXIT returns to the calling file.
The key word FERMER or CLOSE closes the file and returns to 
the calling file.
A file can call an other file, and so on,...
Several levels of files are possible.
